---
import ComingSoonRoomLayout from '../layouts/ComingSoonRoomLayout.astro';
---
<ComingSoonRoomLayout
  room="computer-room"
  title="Computer Room"
  subtitle="Digital resources, research tools."
  sourceId="coming-soon-computer-room"
>
  <p>
    The Computer Room is where the Library's data leaves the page and
    becomes workable. Downloadable datasets in plain CSV and JSON for every
    state in the federal-grant system. Interactive calculators that let a
    citizen compare what their state's trust is worth today against what it
    would have been worth if managed at the federal-trust median rate of
    return. A growing toolkit for researchers — citation generators,
    data-quality flags, version-controlled snapshots of the substrate.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Why this room matters.</strong> Numbers that can only be read in
    their original prose are numbers that don't travel. The Computer Room
    is the room that lets a reporter pull the Oklahoma corpus figure
    straight into a spreadsheet, lets a graduate student run their own
    regression on the data, lets a state legislator's staffer download the
    four-state comparison their boss asked for at four in the afternoon and
    have it on the desk by morning.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Build with us.</strong> An invitation will sit beside every
    dataset: if you build something interesting on the Library's data, send
    it to us, and we will host or link it. The Library grows by
    accumulation.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Being planned.</strong> The first downloadable CSV — the
    era-cohort data — goes up first.
  </p>
</ComingSoonRoomLayout>
